Southern Oregon University/ Stevenson Union Basement
directions: The GN Bathroom is on the 2nd floor of the Stevenson Union on the right side of the dining area across from Elmo's behind the pizza station

name: Southern Oregon University/ Stevenson Union Basement Room 109
directions:
FROM THE STAIRS: Enter Stevenson Union by the book store entrance. Take a right down the stairs. Go through the doors at the bottom of the stairs. Take the first right down the hallway, GN bathroom is on the right 

FROM THE ELEVATOR: Enter the Stevenson Union through the doors by the Commuter Resource Center. The elevator is on the right. Take the elevator down to the basement. exit to the right of the elevator and proceed down the hall. Take the first left down the hallway. The GN bathroom is on the right.

name: Wells Hall, Murray State University
directions: Second floor, around the hall from office 221, by the water fountain
comment: Currently the only gender neutral bathroom on campus, but made specifically with trans people's comfort in mind! :)

name: Colorado School of Mines Arthur Lakes Library
directions: While accessible, it's a third floor restroom, in hallway with offices.  The elevator drops you off on the north side of the building, so you'd have to travel past the book shelves and down an odd side hallway to the correct (South-East side) area.

name: Roundhouse Community Arts and Recreation Centre
street: 181 Roundhouse Mews at Davie Street and Pacific Boulevard
directions: Walk towards the dance hall. One single-stall family washroom is on your right in a small corridor that leads to exhibition hall.
comment: It's sometimes inaccessible during special events.

name: Brauhaus Schmitz
comment: For customers. Restaurant has a dozen individual, unisex stalls as their restroom.

name: Wesleyan College
directions: 3 inclusive bathrooms in main building, OSP (1) top floor to the right next to admissions office, (2) bottom floor to the left next to break room and in between M and F bathrooms, (3) bottom floor on hallway leading out to parking lot
comment: anyone can use them, the building is open to the public

name: Jugo Juice
directions: Enter side door at Davie Street. A single-stall washroom is to your right.
comment: You have to be a paying customer.

name: White Castle
directions: Directly through doors on east side (opposite side of building from Big Bend).
comment: You can slip in and out rather easily of you take the door on the east/right side of the building.

name: Södertörns högskola, 141 52 Huddinge, Sweden
comment: all of the sodertorns university toilets are unisex/gender neutral and can be used for free.

name: Tacobarinn
directions: Gender neutral + accessible single stall on ground floor, gender neutral single stalls on second floor

name: Five Guys
directions: Bathrooms are located at the back of the restaurant
comment: For paying customers

name: Prince George Public Library (Bob Harkins Branch)
directions: On first floor of the library behind the Teen Service Counter in the same small hallway where the other washrooms are.
comment: The door is locked, so you have to ask for the key at the front desks (where you would check out books). Just ask for the key to the gender-neutral bathroom.

name: Portland State University Lincoln Hall
directions:
entering from park blocks: after you go in, open door (either right or left side) to go down a flight of stairs, then turn right to the end of the hall. turn left and it's on your left. it's across from the underground walkway linking lincoln hall & cramer hall

entering from sw market (needs psu student id): go through the 2nd set of doors and go down the hallway that's in front of you (a bit off to your right). turn left at the end of the hall and it's on your left directly across from the underground hallway that links lincoln hall & cramer hall

entering from door facing cramer hall (doors on left side closer to park blocks): go down a flight of stairs, open the door and it should be towards the right almost in front of you
comment: locking single-stalled unisex bathroom, pretty spacious, and not a lot of people in this area of the building so usually vacant and ready for use

name: Seattle Counseling Services
directions: Get out the elevator take a left, then take a left  and go down the hallway and then take the first left you see.

name: The Pleasure Chest
directions: Restroom is the door on the right just before the stairs (the stairway on the left side of the front cash register)
comment: Staff are the friendliest. All sex-positive, trained in gender sensitivity, and several on staff identify as trams or have trans partners. The epitome of welcoming and non-judgement. It's a sex shop though, so those 18+ only are allowed inside.

name: Central Station
directions: First bathroom on the right when exiting platforms

name: SafeHouse Center
directions: you'll see it right when you walk into the lobby! there's a sign on the door that says "all genders"
comment: just be warned that SafeHouse has specific lobby hours, i am only adding SafeHouse because it's obviously a very safe space and worth trying if you're nearby, but there's always a chance that you'll arrive there and the building won't be open to the general public.

name: Harvest pizza
directions: It's a very small restroom and this is the only bathroom!

name: Neutral Zone
directions: upstairs are the gender neutral bathrooms!! ask anyone if you need help finding them! there are also gendered bathrooms downstairs and the neutral zone is a really safe space so that could be an option if you're comfortable with that.
comment: the neutral zone in general is a safe space and i don't think anyone would mind if you used the restroom, but be mindful that the neutral zone is a teen center, so this is an ideal bathroom for a teen to use.

name: Hungry Tiger
directions: One in back, one near bar, both gender neutral.

name: Masonville Mall
directions: 2nd floor near the north-east corner of the building

name: Minneapolis College of Art and Design
directions: In the Morrison building, there are two unisex. The rest of the bathrooms in the school are typically safe places, though!
comment: The school closes to non-students early morning and late night, but if you're visiting for the gallery

name: Crooked Crust
directions: Walk in and walk straight a few paces and the restrooms are to your right by the place where you order.
comment: No one will care if you're a customer but since you're so close to the register I always feel weird about not buying anything.

name: Big Mike's Coffee
directions: Walk in look to your left and two the back. You will see two single stall restrooms
comment: You can walk right in, is the restroom and leave. But they have great coffee too.

name: Killam Memorial Library
directions: Second floor, go up the main staircase, take the door on the left and then make another left and walk straight. Washroom labelled as unisex.

name: Walmart
directions: Usually by layaway/In-Store Pickup
comment: "Family" restroom not labeled for gender

name: Zablocki Library
directions: Located in hall way off of the back exit.
comment: Library has odd hours, but bathroom is large and very easy to use to change in.

name: Aurora St Luke's Medical Center
directions: There is a bathroom located right off of the main hospital entrance by the step on your right hand side.
comment: It's a nice sized bathroom.

name: Light House Cuba Cinema
comment: Multiple unisex single stalls - one is wheelchair accessible. Officially for customers, but should be quite easy to just walk in.

name: Robert Stout Building, Victoria University

comment: 2 single stall, gender neutral, wheelchair accessible toilets.

name: Kirk Building, Victoria University
directions: Two single stall gender neutral toilets on Level 0 - take the lift down or access through the Hunter Courtyard.
comment: Flat access and reasonable size, though not large enough to be wheelchair accessible.

name: Chocolaterian Cafe
comment: Both restrooms are spacious and gender-neutral.

name: The Yellow Deli
directions: Second floor

name: All Souls Unitarian Church
directions: The lower level (accessible by stairs and elevator) has three individual unisex bathrooms, with potentially a fourth on the way.
comment: The bathrooms were an intentional part of a multimillion dollar renovation aimed at increasing the church's diversity and inclusion efforts.  Feel free to ask for direction from the reception desk at the entrance on Harvard St.!

name: University of Sydney, Queer Space

name: Buckhead Coffeehouse

comment: I think you have to pay but a cheap muffin or coffee isn't a big deal.

name: International Film School Sydney

name: University of North Texas Crumley Hall
